WEBVTT

00:02.003 --> 00:03.435
        [ Remote clicks ]

00:03.437 --> 00:05.037
     [ Upbeat music plays ]

00:07.508 --> 00:10.442
 � I don't care what you say! �

00:11.712 --> 00:13.712
   � I'm gonna do what I want
           all day! �

00:13.714 --> 00:16.347
  � I'm the king of the world!
  I'm the king of the world! �

00:16.350 --> 00:18.283
   � I'm the king of the world!
   I'm the king of the world! �

00:18.285 --> 00:22.921
  � I'm the king of the world!
  I'm the king of the world! �

00:28.562 --> 00:32.031
  [ Indistinct conversations ]

00:34.702 --> 00:36.235
  Hey, gather around, children.

00:36.237 --> 00:37.536
  Okay, all right,
   guys, today --

00:37.538 --> 00:39.505
              Just let me know
           if you need anything.

00:39.507 --> 00:41.206
  [ Clears throat ]
 Thank you. Thanks.

00:41.208 --> 00:44.510
Uh, today's group project
will be for our annual

00:44.512 --> 00:47.146
Grow and Show Environment
  Awareness Month.

00:47.148 --> 00:49.581
   Okay, we'll be
 working in pairs...

00:49.583 --> 00:52.217
          [ Cheering ]

00:52.219 --> 00:53.752
          Our class has
     an odd number of kids,

00:53.754 --> 00:54.920
 so we can be a group of three!

00:54.922 --> 00:56.355
Just like Kids 2 Dudes!

00:56.357 --> 00:59.525
       Except, this time,
I'm going to pick your partners.

00:59.527 --> 01:00.926
          [ All groan ]

01:00.928 --> 01:01.927
        Okay, okay, okay.

01:01.929 --> 01:03.262
      Okay, so here goes...

01:03.264 --> 01:04.663
            Clarence.

01:04.665 --> 01:06.498
                         Yeah!
            And Sumo.

01:06.500 --> 01:07.766
      Oh, yeah.

01:07.768 --> 01:08.767
      Uh, what?

01:08.769 --> 01:10.602
             I'm your new daddy!

01:10.604 --> 01:12.271
              Coochie-coochie,
                coo-coo-coo!

01:12.273 --> 01:14.440
  And then we got, uh, Jeff...

01:14.442 --> 01:17.609
             [ Humming happily ]

01:17.611 --> 01:19.044
         ...and Belson.

01:19.046 --> 01:20.946
          [ Giggling ]
     Courtlin and Malessica.

01:20.948 --> 01:22.081
      Yay!
                       Yay!

01:22.083 --> 01:23.082
          [ Giggling ]

01:23.084 --> 01:26.085
     Kimby and, uh, Chelsea.

01:27.188 --> 01:29.088
        S'up?

01:29.090 --> 01:30.889
           Look at you
       in your little pot.

01:30.891 --> 01:32.624
 You're a cutie pie, aren't you?

01:32.626 --> 01:34.393
      I'm gonna call you...

01:34.395 --> 01:35.627
            Pot-pie.

01:35.629 --> 01:38.964
Sumo, do you think that's a good
    name for our little one?

01:38.966 --> 01:40.799
              Sumo?

01:40.801 --> 01:41.800
                    What?

01:41.802 --> 01:43.235
              Hmm.

01:43.237 --> 01:44.870
       Do you think she'll
     get that big one day --

01:44.872 --> 01:45.971
     with birds in her hair?

01:45.973 --> 01:47.139
    [ Harp plays glissando ]

01:47.141 --> 01:48.807
                  It's just
            a little shrub weed.

01:48.809 --> 01:51.477
 My mom makes me pluck a million
       of them, like, every day.

01:51.479 --> 01:55.280
Yeah, but Pot-pie is special,
 'cause she's ours.

01:57.318 --> 02:00.285
              Jeff:
    I will name you Specimen.

02:00.287 --> 02:03.455
I've already drawn up plans for
a growth zone in my bedroom.

02:03.457 --> 02:05.491
Oh, and here's a list of
supplies that we'll need.

02:05.493 --> 02:07.459
     First off,
we'll need better soil.

02:07.461 --> 02:08.494
       Belson?

02:08.496 --> 02:10.895
                  What? Oh.
         Were you talking to me?

02:10.898 --> 02:13.432
            Yeah, I don't really
              care about that.

02:13.434 --> 02:15.100
       But we have to get
       all these supplies

02:15.102 --> 02:16.668
     to be sure we reach our
     plant growth potential.

02:16.670 --> 02:20.005
Uh, here, just take my allowance
and get us an "A" or whatever.

02:20.007 --> 02:22.307
                 Wow, quite
          the generous donation.

02:22.309 --> 02:23.609
          I'll be sure to invest

02:23.611 --> 02:25.978
             in the top-quality
             gardening supplies.

02:25.980 --> 02:27.079
         We could name him Joey!

02:27.081 --> 02:28.480
     I love it!

02:28.482 --> 02:30.415
       Together: Aw, yay!
     Joey, Joey, Joey, Joey!

02:30.417 --> 02:33.352
               So, what should
                 we name it?

02:33.354 --> 02:35.154
      Oh. Um...

02:35.156 --> 02:37.689
What about Princess Plant?

02:37.691 --> 02:39.491
               That's...cool.

02:39.493 --> 02:41.293
              But what about --

02:41.295 --> 02:43.862
                 [ Laughs ]
                Cinnamon Gum?

02:43.864 --> 02:45.030
        Um...

02:45.032 --> 02:47.666
            Hey, check this out!

02:47.668 --> 02:48.800
       [ Sharpie squeaks ]

02:48.802 --> 02:50.536
               I'm Mr. Leafse!

02:50.538 --> 02:51.603
          [ Muttering ]

02:51.605 --> 02:53.839
You better water me,
or that's a detention!

02:53.841 --> 02:55.340
           [ Giggles ]

02:55.342 --> 02:57.943
  Clarence: "There are too many
       turtles in my home.

02:57.945 --> 03:00.512
   [ Imitating truck engine ]
  Too many turtles for a gnome.

03:00.514 --> 03:03.048
 Get these turtles out the door.

03:03.050 --> 03:05.884
   I can't even see my floor!"

03:05.886 --> 03:07.619
 Wow, look at all those turtles.

03:07.621 --> 03:09.788
        Say, it would be
   pretty hard to walk around.

03:09.790 --> 03:13.825
Sumo, I think Pot-pie wants her
other daddy to read a page.

03:13.827 --> 03:15.494
                 Huh, what?!
              No, that's dumb.

03:15.496 --> 03:17.229
               I'm not reading
              to a dumb plant.

03:17.231 --> 03:18.397
        Sumo!

03:18.399 --> 03:19.231
        Shh!

03:19.233 --> 03:20.699
  She can hear you!

03:20.701 --> 03:23.168
She's a living person,
just like you and me.

03:23.170 --> 03:25.037
  Reading will help
  her grow better.

03:25.039 --> 03:26.138
        Here.

03:26.140 --> 03:27.306
       Plants don't have brains.

03:27.308 --> 03:29.341
   Just do it.
                    I said no.

03:29.343 --> 03:31.210
 Come on, trust me.
Just -- just one page.

03:31.212 --> 03:32.244
         I said I don't want to.

03:32.246 --> 03:34.279
    Come on!
                     I said no!

03:35.316 --> 03:37.749
[ Gasps ] Sumo, our Pot-pie
 has a boo-boo now!

03:37.751 --> 03:39.184
                  Oh, man!

03:39.186 --> 03:40.886
             Oh, I wasn't trying
         to hurt the dang thing!

03:40.888 --> 03:42.421
Don't touch her anymore!
                            Ow!

03:42.423 --> 03:45.023
     Jeff: I'll probably get
some sort of record for, like...

03:45.025 --> 03:47.359
   like huge plant, you know?

03:47.361 --> 03:50.495
  Like Jack and the beanstalk?

03:50.497 --> 03:53.832
  [ Electronic sound effects ]

03:53.834 --> 03:55.934
      [ Rock music plays ]
     Robot voice: Robofrog!

03:55.936 --> 03:57.936
    Rise of the Ribbetarians.

03:57.938 --> 04:00.038
         Those are new.

04:00.040 --> 04:01.273
               Hi.

04:01.275 --> 04:03.575
   I'm just gonna take a look.

04:03.577 --> 04:05.244
         [ Bell chimes ]

04:07.381 --> 04:09.114
     Plants need play, too.

04:09.116 --> 04:10.249
       Here you go, buddy.

04:10.251 --> 04:12.451
       Fun equals growth.

04:12.453 --> 04:13.919
      Mmm, oh.

04:13.921 --> 04:16.088
      Come on.

04:16.089 --> 04:17.555
       Oh, no.

04:17.558 --> 04:18.690
                    Ohhh.

04:18.692 --> 04:20.791
Oh, hey, you working
on your plant project?

04:20.793 --> 04:24.196
  Yeah, but our little Pot-pie
     is not looking so good.

04:24.198 --> 04:26.131
            It needs tough love!

04:26.133 --> 04:28.133
             Leave it in the sun
        so it learns its lesson.

04:28.135 --> 04:30.135
            Nah, bud.
     You got to nurture it.

04:30.137 --> 04:31.136
              Whoa.

04:31.138 --> 04:32.704
       Snapped stem, huh?

04:35.809 --> 04:37.309
             What are you doing?

04:37.311 --> 04:39.378
Oh, well, Chad used to
   work on a farm

04:39.380 --> 04:40.646
where they grew plants.

04:40.648 --> 04:41.647
            You did?

04:41.649 --> 04:43.282
            Oh, yeah, for years.

04:43.284 --> 04:45.651
        Oh, it was a great time.

04:46.987 --> 04:49.621
      Okay, this and, yeah.

04:49.623 --> 04:50.789
       There you go, bud.

04:50.791 --> 04:51.990
           All fixed.

04:51.992 --> 04:53.592
                You're okay,
               shrubby-dubby.

04:53.594 --> 04:55.394
    Aw. Pot-pie.

04:55.396 --> 04:57.296
              Wow.
          Thanks, Chad.

04:57.298 --> 04:58.897
  You know, part of
raising a baby plant --

04:58.899 --> 05:01.400
or a baby anything -- is asking
for help when you need it.

05:01.402 --> 05:02.901
No one can do it alone.

05:02.903 --> 05:05.504
            So true. Yeah, I got
      lots of gardening supplies

05:05.506 --> 05:07.272
       in the garage if you want
               to borrow them.

05:07.274 --> 05:09.908
  [ Giggles ] Chad.
Such a green thumb, over here.

05:09.910 --> 05:12.744
                  Oh. Mare.

05:12.746 --> 05:14.246
              So...

05:14.248 --> 05:15.847
       is this your room?

05:15.849 --> 05:17.849
        It's really pink.

05:17.851 --> 05:19.484
                  Uh, yeah.

05:19.486 --> 05:20.452
                   It is.

05:20.454 --> 05:23.322
    Oh, man! This
werewolf poster is sick!

05:23.324 --> 05:25.691
Does this guy, like,
hunt humans in the night

05:25.693 --> 05:27.759
 and tear them apart
     and stuff?

05:27.761 --> 05:29.027
                   Uh, no.

05:29.029 --> 05:31.129
              He's a boyfriend.

05:31.131 --> 05:34.433
Oh, that's cool, too.

05:34.435 --> 05:36.768
        Whoa!
Kimby, did you paint this?

05:36.770 --> 05:37.869
                    Yeah.

05:37.871 --> 05:38.870
        How?

05:38.872 --> 05:40.839
                Um, I just...

05:42.142 --> 05:44.276
          [ Grunting ]

05:45.112 --> 05:46.144
                 That's it.

05:46.146 --> 05:47.612
 Kimby, that's rad.

05:47.614 --> 05:48.780
                   Uh, oh.

05:48.782 --> 05:49.781
              Thanks, Chelsea.

05:49.783 --> 05:50.849
    Oh, you're --

05:50.851 --> 05:52.617
               Oh. [ Giggles ]

05:52.619 --> 05:54.186
    Can you paint
  a werewolf next?

05:54.188 --> 05:55.487
        Sure, I can try!

05:55.489 --> 05:58.557
               Make him, like,
           foaming at the mouth.

05:58.559 --> 06:00.826
        Oh, yeah, I really think
          being around her peers

06:00.828 --> 06:02.994
               is stimulating
             Josephine's growth.

06:02.996 --> 06:04.863
                 Hey, honey.

06:07.034 --> 06:10.335
             No, slower! Slower!

06:10.337 --> 06:13.071
     Oh, please,
    try the brie.

06:13.073 --> 06:14.406
                  Oh, thank you.
               Ew!

06:14.408 --> 06:16.641
              You know, you two
         are so good with yours.

06:16.643 --> 06:19.144
           How do we get Pot-pie
         as big as Frankenstein?

06:19.146 --> 06:20.645
              That is amazing.

06:20.647 --> 06:22.914
       Ah, Pot-pie's just
    our little late bloomer.

06:22.916 --> 06:24.316
         Oh.

06:25.652 --> 06:27.753
        [ Jeff chuckles ]

06:27.755 --> 06:31.223
       Oh, jeez. Specimen,
   you're not looking so good.

06:32.760 --> 06:36.361
         Things are going great,
but, uh, to continue this level,

06:36.363 --> 06:39.831
               of, uh growth,
         higher and ever higher,

06:39.833 --> 06:41.433
           we need more capital.

06:41.435 --> 06:42.934
   What -- oh, for
  the plant thing?

06:42.936 --> 06:45.570
 Yeah, sure, as long
  as we get an "A."

06:45.572 --> 06:47.339
           Let's try this again.

06:49.009 --> 06:50.208
        I have a problem.

06:50.210 --> 06:52.277
      [ Soft music plays ]

06:52.279 --> 06:53.512
        [ Bell clanging ]

06:53.514 --> 07:00.051
    � Hush, little seedling �

07:00.053 --> 07:06.792
     � Hush, little thing �

07:06.794 --> 07:11.530
  � Tenderly, we care for you �

07:11.532 --> 07:13.932
                    Shh.

07:13.934 --> 07:19.704
      � Tenderly, we sing �

07:20.641 --> 07:27.479
    � Hush, little seedling �

07:27.481 --> 07:34.286
      � Hush, little song �

07:34.288 --> 07:41.159
� Gently, we will care for you �

07:41.161 --> 07:46.865
    � Gently, you will grow �

07:48.936 --> 07:50.168
            [ Sighs ]

07:50.170 --> 07:52.471
      Just tell the truth.

07:54.007 --> 07:55.340
   Okay, I'm here.

07:55.342 --> 07:56.975
    What the heck
  was so important?

07:56.977 --> 07:58.009
      It's about Specimen.

07:58.011 --> 07:59.077
   I'm afraid she's taken ill.

07:59.079 --> 08:00.345
                    Who?

08:00.347 --> 08:02.681
  I'm sorry to say
 it was no accident.

08:02.683 --> 08:03.915
      I, um...

08:03.917 --> 08:06.284
  I spent the money
you gave me on those.

08:06.286 --> 08:07.752
I'm so sorry, Belson.

08:07.754 --> 08:10.255
I just I -- I couldn't
  help myself and--

08:10.257 --> 08:11.823
        Are these from Robofrog?
     What?

08:11.825 --> 08:13.792
               Yeah, I've been
           playing the new game.

08:13.794 --> 08:14.793
               Who's this guy?

08:14.795 --> 08:16.294
                I don't think
          I've unlocked him yet.

08:16.296 --> 08:17.462
        O-oh.

08:17.464 --> 08:19.831
Um, that's Martanus.

08:19.833 --> 08:23.101
He's an inter-dimensional
  cyborg gladiator.

08:23.103 --> 08:24.536
                    Cool.

08:24.538 --> 08:28.206
You know, actually, why don't
you keep that one, Belson?

08:28.208 --> 08:30.842
                Well, duh --
        I'm keeping all of them.

08:30.844 --> 08:32.110
    That's fair.

08:32.111 --> 08:35.347
       Hmm. I'd say we did
     a pretty good job here

08:35.349 --> 08:36.982
with our little Pot-pie.

08:36.984 --> 08:38.316
                We sure did.

08:38.318 --> 08:41.553
   Uh, Clarence, try rocking her
          a little softer, okay?

08:41.554 --> 08:43.722
    [ Scoffs ] I think I know
   how to rock Pot-pie, Sumo.

08:43.724 --> 08:45.624
   You're doing it
  all herky-jerky.

08:45.626 --> 08:47.893
She likes it smooth,
     like this.

08:47.895 --> 08:50.562
            No, that's too much.
        She's gonna get seasick.

08:50.564 --> 08:51.796
  Clarence, let go!

08:51.798 --> 08:53.298
                Not until you
           rock her right, Sumo.

08:53.300 --> 08:55.400
   Come on, move!
                         Fine.

08:55.402 --> 08:56.902
          [ Both gasp ]

08:56.904 --> 08:59.638
          [ Screaming ]

09:02.743 --> 09:05.243
           Next is...

09:05.245 --> 09:06.344
        Jeff and Belson.

09:06.346 --> 09:07.345
          [ Chuckles nervously ]

09:07.347 --> 09:08.513
      Oh, looks pretty g--

09:08.515 --> 09:10.315
           Wait. Hmm.

09:10.317 --> 09:12.150
    Guys, the assignment was
         to take care of

09:12.152 --> 09:14.519
      the plant I gave you,
     not to buy another one.

09:14.521 --> 09:17.222
                   Uh, oh.
            What was I thinking?

09:17.224 --> 09:18.690
     [ Scoffs ]
  Jeff, who cares?

09:18.692 --> 09:20.825
                      Belson!
Just -- just give us a "C."

09:20.827 --> 09:22.394
                   Belson,
        that's not what I meant.

09:22.396 --> 09:23.995
          Fine, give us
      a "D," I don't care.

09:23.997 --> 09:26.598
Don't even put those ideas
in her mind, you sick pup.

09:26.600 --> 09:27.832
              Boys, calm down.

09:27.834 --> 09:29.267
       Okay, we'll talk about it
                after class.

09:29.269 --> 09:31.102
                Okay, now...

09:31.104 --> 09:32.938
             Chelsea and Kimby.

09:32.940 --> 09:34.105
                  Uh, okay.

09:34.107 --> 09:35.941
           You guys didn't raise
             a successful plant,

09:35.943 --> 09:38.376
     but you seem to have gotten
       along great and made a...

09:38.378 --> 09:39.511
              whatever this is.

09:39.513 --> 09:40.779
     So that's pretty good.

09:40.781 --> 09:45.116
          And, finally,
       Sumo and Clarence.

09:45.118 --> 09:46.284
              Hmm.

09:46.286 --> 09:48.019
      Despite your plant's
          unique look,

09:48.021 --> 09:49.788
  you -- you guys actually did
       a pretty good job.

09:49.790 --> 09:51.790
     Well, everybody, I hope
 you learned a little something

09:51.792 --> 09:53.792
         about teamwork
     and raising something,

09:53.794 --> 09:56.094
  you know, from a small seed.

09:56.096 --> 09:58.530
         You guys ready
     to plant these things?

09:58.532 --> 10:01.299
           [ Humming ]

10:01.301 --> 10:03.101
    Ha. Awesome.

10:03.103 --> 10:04.836
What do you think, Kimby?

10:05.639 --> 10:08.406
              Wow. You're guys'
              plant is so cool.

10:08.408 --> 10:09.407
              Yeah.

10:09.409 --> 10:10.575
                     No!

10:10.577 --> 10:11.977
           You're smothering it.

10:11.979 --> 10:13.712
              He can't breathe!

10:15.916 --> 10:18.316
     Okay, bud,
  ready to do this?

10:18.318 --> 10:20.919
             [ Sniffles ] Yeah.
                 I'm ready.

10:20.921 --> 10:22.087
                  No, wait!

10:22.089 --> 10:25.123
             Oh, Pot-pie, we're
         gonna miss you so much.

10:25.125 --> 10:26.625
          Don't forget about us.

10:26.627 --> 10:29.294
             Be safe -- and make
              lots of friends.

10:29.296 --> 10:30.495
                [ Smooches ]

10:30.497 --> 10:32.297
                Oh, they said
        this day was gonna come,

10:32.299 --> 10:34.833
    but I never thought it would
          be like this. [ Sobs ]

10:34.835 --> 10:38.236
Ah, come on, man, you're
gonna make me start crying.

10:38.238 --> 10:40.405
         And here's your book...

10:40.407 --> 10:43.308
                [Stammering]
       ...in case you get bored.

10:43.310 --> 10:50.081
         It's your favorite with
      the gnome and the turtles.

10:50.083 --> 10:51.650
            Oh, guys!

10:51.652 --> 10:54.819
   Your garden looks so good!

10:54.821 --> 10:58.123
Kind of makes you think about
 settling down, hmm?

10:58.125 --> 11:00.325
              No, it doesn't --
               no, not at all.

11:00.327 --> 11:01.760
      [ Blows nose loudly ]

11:01.762 --> 11:03.061
       Oh, okay, Clarence,
         that's enough.

11:04.431 --> 11:06.364
        � Early to bed �

11:07.801 --> 11:10.535
        � Early to rise �

11:11.371 --> 11:13.872
       � Picking my nose �

11:17.644 --> 11:21.680
                     ��

11:21.682 --> 11:23.014
           Ms. Baker:
           "But, soft!

11:23.016 --> 11:25.350
           What light
  through yonder window breaks?

11:25.352 --> 11:28.953
         It is the east,
     and Juliet is the sun."

11:28.955 --> 11:30.221
        [ Knock on door ]
              Uh...

11:30.223 --> 11:31.156
                Knock, knock!

11:31.158 --> 11:32.991
Oh, right -- the thing.
    Come on in!

11:32.993 --> 11:35.226
Okay, everyone, please give
your attention to Mr. Jones.

11:35.228 --> 11:37.162
      He's got
a <i> very</i> special announcement.

11:37.164 --> 11:38.163
           Hey, there!

11:38.165 --> 11:39.964
       Today after school,
        we're performing

11:39.966 --> 11:43.501
       the school musical,
      "Bucky and the Howl"!

11:43.503 --> 11:44.836
 We have a musical?

11:44.838 --> 11:46.204
    We have an amazing group

11:46.206 --> 11:48.406
    who've been working hard
     for the past two weeks,

11:48.408 --> 11:51.643
         including a lot
  of your brilliant classmates.

11:51.645 --> 11:53.078
         What?! Really?!
          [ Murmuring ]

11:53.080 --> 11:55.346
             Who would ever want
to be in a play? That's so lame.

11:55.348 --> 11:58.316
          So, if anyone
  wants to join our production,

11:58.318 --> 12:00.852
    come by at recess, lunch,
         or...whenever!

12:00.854 --> 12:02.754
              Uh...
      we've got doughnuts.

12:02.756 --> 12:04.823
    Oh, my gosh!
  I love doughnuts!

12:04.825 --> 12:08.793
Aren't you guys excited
to see the...fun play?

12:09.529 --> 12:11.996
  Come on. I'm sure
last year's was...great. Right?

12:11.998 --> 12:13.031
Did...anyone see it?

12:13.033 --> 12:15.100
        I didn't see it.
             Sorry.

12:15.102 --> 12:19.504
         Okay. So, we'll see you
 after school in the gymatorium!

12:21.374 --> 12:22.707
                Okay, Nathan.

12:22.709 --> 12:25.343
    We practiced this with Sumo,
but we can't find him right now.

12:25.345 --> 12:28.113
 But you're pretty much a bigger
        Sumo, so we'll be great.

12:28.115 --> 12:30.582
           All right,
       four-legged racers.

12:30.584 --> 12:32.851
  On your four-legged marks...

12:32.853 --> 12:35.420
     get four-legged set...

12:35.422 --> 12:37.288
               go!

12:37.290 --> 12:38.389
                   [ Grunting ]

12:38.391 --> 12:39.390
       Nathan!

12:39.392 --> 12:41.059
                Nathan, stop it!
We can't get up! Stop!

12:41.061 --> 12:43.795
          This is supposed to be
       a team-building exercise!

12:43.797 --> 12:45.563
 [ Clarence and Jeff groaning ]

12:45.565 --> 12:47.599
       [ Group cheering ]

12:47.601 --> 12:48.700
               Aw!

12:48.702 --> 12:51.202
          Sorry, guys.
          I biffed it.

12:51.204 --> 12:52.270
                That's okay.

12:52.272 --> 12:54.105
        You're always a champion
                 in <i> my</i> eyes.

12:54.107 --> 12:56.074
          Thanks, man.
      I really needed that.

12:56.076 --> 12:57.776
        When you asked me
      to fill in for Sumo,

12:57.778 --> 12:59.410
     I got a little nervous,
           because...

12:59.412 --> 13:01.780
       Hmm. That's a good point.
          Where <i> is</i> Sumo, anyhow?

13:01.782 --> 13:03.915
     ...haven't been getting
   a lot of support at home...

13:03.917 --> 13:05.884
         so I'm kind of
        on edge today...

13:05.886 --> 13:07.452
                 Sumo? Hmm?

13:07.454 --> 13:08.720
                Wrong shoes.

13:08.722 --> 13:10.121
               Wrong shoes.

13:10.123 --> 13:11.122
                    Sumo!

13:11.124 --> 13:12.056
                     Oh.

13:12.058 --> 13:13.658
     He didn't
even stop by to eat

13:13.660 --> 13:15.593
    his afternoon
 trash breadsticks.

13:15.595 --> 13:17.162
        Sumo!

13:17.164 --> 13:18.163
                    Sumo!

13:18.165 --> 13:19.330
        Sumo!

13:19.332 --> 13:20.932
     [ Mid-tempo music plays ]
Where are you, Sumo?

13:20.934 --> 13:21.966
   Echoooo!
              Huh?

13:21.968 --> 13:24.002
              Ooh.
    Hmm.

13:27.340 --> 13:30.308
              Where, oh, where
       could that darn coyote...

13:30.310 --> 13:31.409
                     be?

13:34.781 --> 13:36.781
            [ Howls ]

13:36.783 --> 13:38.583
  Oh, my goodness!

13:38.585 --> 13:39.951
           [ Growls ]

13:39.953 --> 13:43.321
     � I'm a hungry coyote,
         hear me growl �

13:43.323 --> 13:47.292
    � 'Cause it's eating time
   and I found me some chow �

13:47.294 --> 13:48.092
    Click, click.

13:48.094 --> 13:49.260
   Hee-haw, Bucky.

13:49.262 --> 13:51.462
     Looks like
you've reached the end.

13:51.464 --> 13:55.800
Wait! The firework be-gifted
to me by the friendly native!

13:55.802 --> 13:57.602
     I'm saved!

13:57.604 --> 13:59.204
        Aah!

13:59.206 --> 14:01.339
    [ Dramatic music plays ]
[ Gasps ] Oh, no!

14:01.341 --> 14:03.474
     Okay, Sumo.
Remember the script.

14:03.476 --> 14:04.475
                 [ Growls ]
      Aah!

14:04.477 --> 14:06.477
                [ Growling ]

14:06.479 --> 14:07.478
        [ Cloth ripping ]

14:07.480 --> 14:08.813
      [ Gasps ]

14:08.815 --> 14:10.481
  [ Growls ]
              Aah!

14:10.483 --> 14:12.483
                [ Growling ]

14:12.485 --> 14:13.985
         This is great.
         This is great!

14:13.987 --> 14:16.354
        Awooooooooooooo!

14:16.356 --> 14:18.489
 [ Jeff and Clarence laughing ]

14:18.491 --> 14:19.324
       Bravo!

14:19.326 --> 14:21.426
   [ Trance-like music plays ]

14:24.965 --> 14:27.498
        Aw, man. I can't believe
              you guys saw me.

14:27.500 --> 14:31.169
               Uh, look, guys,
can you not tell anyone? Please?

14:31.171 --> 14:32.570
Well, I thought you looked
pretty good up there.

14:32.572 --> 14:36.040
    Yeah, Sumo. I never knew
      you could do...that.

14:36.042 --> 14:38.543
            So...you don't think
                  I'm lame?

14:38.545 --> 14:42.714
No way! You were all like,
"Rawr! I'm a coyote!"

14:42.716 --> 14:43.715
      [ Howls ]

14:43.717 --> 14:45.049
  Uhp! [ Chuckles ]

14:45.051 --> 14:47.151
            Well, thanks for not
         making fun of me, guys.

14:47.153 --> 14:48.519
      It's actually kind of fun.

14:48.521 --> 14:51.589
            Mr. Jones lets me do
       all kinds of crazy stuff.

14:51.591 --> 14:53.524
           So how come
     you're so embarrassed?

14:53.526 --> 14:55.526
          Well, 'cause everybody
               except you guys

14:55.528 --> 14:56.828
          thinks plays are lame.

14:56.830 --> 14:58.897
         I'm just happy nobody's
         gonna come to this play

14:58.899 --> 15:00.365
                 and see me
               being all lame.

15:00.367 --> 15:01.532
                       Ah! Sumo!

15:01.534 --> 15:04.269
           That last run-through
             was truly inspired.

15:04.271 --> 15:07.071
   Although I think you may have
    scared off our Bucky O'Neil.

15:07.073 --> 15:09.173
      Un...pro...fessional!

15:09.175 --> 15:10.775
       [ Grunts ] I quit!

15:10.777 --> 15:12.343
                Besides Rita,

15:12.345 --> 15:14.946
            you're the only <i> true</i>
         tour de force up there.

15:14.948 --> 15:16.881
        Jeff,
<i> you</i> should join the play.

15:16.883 --> 15:19.017
                 [ Coughs ]
                  W-What?!

15:19.019 --> 15:21.019
Just think about it, Jeff.
   Imagine you --

15:21.021 --> 15:22.587
             Oh, what the heck?
             I'll give it a try.

15:22.589 --> 15:26.190
      How about some simple
 "Twinkle, Twinkle Little Star"?

15:26.192 --> 15:28.226
         [ Music plays ]

15:28.228 --> 15:30.561
          [ Wheezing ]
             Jeff, are you okay?

15:30.563 --> 15:33.131
           It's fine.
    I just -- I'm a baritone.

15:33.133 --> 15:35.733
        Could you go down
           an octave?

15:35.735 --> 15:37.936
  [ Music plays in lower key ]

15:37.938 --> 15:40.204
           [ Muffled ]
     It's too fast. Slower.

15:40.206 --> 15:42.573
         [ Tempo slows ]

15:42.575 --> 15:43.775
     [ Whispering ] Slower.

15:43.777 --> 15:46.311
      [ Single note plays ]
       [ Rapid footsteps ]

15:47.914 --> 15:49.080
    [ Grunting ]

15:49.082 --> 15:50.648
            Clarence!

15:50.650 --> 15:52.383
           [ Off-key ]
     � Bucky and the Howl �

15:52.385 --> 15:55.086
        � One's a coyote
   and the other one's a man �

15:55.088 --> 15:56.487
  � Coyote's comin' after you �

15:56.489 --> 15:58.957
       � Yeah, he'll kick
       your little butt �

15:58.959 --> 15:59.958
              Cha!

15:59.960 --> 16:01.492
          [ Cheering ]

16:01.494 --> 16:04.729
      Ladies and gentlemen,
    we have found our Bucky!

16:04.731 --> 16:07.265
           Mr. Jones:
   We put our hearts into it,

16:07.267 --> 16:10.068
   that merry band of misfits.

16:10.070 --> 16:11.769
      We thirsted for art,

16:11.771 --> 16:13.237
         for admiration.

16:13.239 --> 16:15.273
   We <i> lived</i> for the curtain --

16:15.275 --> 16:17.275
                    Um...
         who are you talking to?

16:17.277 --> 16:18.776
         For my memoirs.

16:18.778 --> 16:21.346
        Okay, everybody!
 Let's try the fireworks scene!

16:21.348 --> 16:22.981
           And, Sumo,
       you're doing great!

16:22.983 --> 16:25.616
  Has someone let a wild coyote
      onstage? [ Chuckles ]

16:25.618 --> 16:28.486
 But just for fun, let's try it
      as <i> written</i> this time

16:28.488 --> 16:30.621
        and let Clarence
      set off the firework.

16:30.623 --> 16:31.622
                Aw, come on!

16:31.624 --> 16:33.291
                A real coyote
          would never get scared

16:33.293 --> 16:34.826
                  by a dumb
              old firecracker!

16:34.828 --> 16:38.129
   Noted. But in the interest
  of not losing another Bucky,

16:38.131 --> 16:39.964
        let's just try it
            this way.

16:39.966 --> 16:41.199
                  Oh, fine.

16:41.201 --> 16:42.934
               No one's gonna
           see this play anyway.

16:42.936 --> 16:46.471
      [ Keyboard plays ]
    � I'm a hungry coyote,
        hear me growl �

16:46.473 --> 16:50.375
    � 'Cause it's eating time
   and I found me some chow �

16:50.377 --> 16:52.610
     [ Stilted ]
Well, Bucky, old pal,

16:52.612 --> 16:58.483
looks like we're...probably
gonna be...um...dead now.

16:58.485 --> 16:59.851
                 Um...rawr!

16:59.853 --> 17:03.688
 Wait! The fireworks
from <i> before</i> in the play!

17:03.690 --> 17:04.789
     I'm saved!

17:05.791 --> 17:07.290
                   Oh, no.

17:07.292 --> 17:09.160
         Come on, Sumo.
       Give me something.

17:09.162 --> 17:10.728
                    Yeah,
        but I don't feel scared.

17:10.730 --> 17:14.165
          Then dig down
   and find me something else.

17:14.166 --> 17:16.134
             Raa-a-a-wr...ohh...

17:16.136 --> 17:17.868
           Dig deeper.
           Go for it!

17:17.871 --> 17:20.972
              Raaaaaaaaaaaawr!

17:20.973 --> 17:23.907
         [ Laughing maniacally ]

17:23.910 --> 17:25.175
[ Laughing continues ]

17:25.178 --> 17:26.176
      [ Howls ]

17:26.179 --> 17:27.478
           Brilliant!

17:27.480 --> 17:29.213
     I don't understand it,
        and it's perfect!

17:29.215 --> 17:30.748
               Good job, Sumo!

17:30.750 --> 17:31.983
         This is gonna be great.

17:31.985 --> 17:34.185
              Oh, I can't wait
     for all our friends to see.

17:34.187 --> 17:36.387
No! You can't tell anyone
 about it, remember?

17:36.389 --> 17:39.023
       But you're doing so good.
      Everyone's gonna love you.

17:39.025 --> 17:41.859
Nobody's gonna nothin' me,
'cause nobody's gonna see me,

17:41.861 --> 17:44.362
  'cause you're not
gonna say anything, right?

17:44.364 --> 17:47.265
             Don't worry, Sumo.
   I'll keep your little secret.

17:47.267 --> 17:51.035
         [ Murmuring ]
      Super special secret
     surprise mystery guest...

17:51.037 --> 17:52.703
     today only at the play!

17:52.705 --> 17:53.604
           Here ya go.

17:53.606 --> 17:55.506
              Here!
    Come see me in the play.

17:55.508 --> 17:57.442
 Starting in 10 minutes, though,
     so you better hurry up.

17:57.444 --> 18:00.078
Hey, are you coming to the play?
        You bet you are.

18:00.080 --> 18:01.345
[ Breathing deeply ]

18:01.347 --> 18:03.014
     Jeff! Play! Now! Here!

18:03.016 --> 18:04.115
      Oh. Okay.

18:04.117 --> 18:05.516
        Sumo:
 Clarence, you told!

18:05.518 --> 18:07.051
  [ Voice cracks ]
  Everyone's here!

18:07.053 --> 18:08.453
             It's not <i> everyone.</i>

18:08.455 --> 18:10.388
             It's just Chelsea,
                  Mavis...

18:10.390 --> 18:13.891
         Belson, Gilben, Julien,
            Guyler, Malessica...

18:13.893 --> 18:15.293
              Marley, Ashley...

18:15.295 --> 18:17.929
[ Vomiting ]
          ...Dunkin, Ms. Baker,
                   Amy --

18:17.931 --> 18:19.564
        Sumo?

18:19.566 --> 18:20.565
       W-Wha?

18:20.567 --> 18:21.933
  What do you mean
     he's gone?

18:21.935 --> 18:23.568
         He got all weirder out.

18:23.570 --> 18:24.902
      [ Sighs ]

18:24.904 --> 18:27.905
It's always the most talented
that contain the most fire.

18:27.907 --> 18:29.073
                 What are we
                  gonna do?

18:29.075 --> 18:31.042
     One of you
is gonna have to fill in!

18:31.744 --> 18:33.744
            But we can't do this
                without Sumo.

18:33.746 --> 18:36.147
    Listen to me.
 It's up to <i> you</i> now.

18:36.149 --> 18:38.149
The show must go on.

18:38.151 --> 18:40.118
      [ Excited murmuring ]

18:40.120 --> 18:41.819
           [ Static ]
       Okay. Cue curtain.

18:43.957 --> 18:45.456
           Cue lights.

18:47.060 --> 18:48.559
       Patsie:
   Hey, watch it!

18:50.130 --> 18:52.864
   [ Trance-like music plays ]

18:55.568 --> 18:56.934
       Sumo: <i> You imbecile!</i>

18:56.936 --> 18:58.836
         <i> Everyone knows</i>
      <i> you're in the play.</i>

18:58.838 --> 19:01.105
          <i> [ Singsong ]</i>
   <i> You're in the stupid play!</i>

19:01.107 --> 19:02.340
        <i> You're so lame.</i>

19:02.342 --> 19:03.941
      <i> Look! What a lame-o.</i>

19:03.943 --> 19:05.176
      <i> You're in the play!</i>

19:05.178 --> 19:07.678
          <i> [ Laughter ]</i>

19:09.315 --> 19:12.517
      [ Grunting, panting ]

19:14.988 --> 19:17.421
      [ Breathing shakily ]

19:19.092 --> 19:22.460
      Aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaah!!

19:22.462 --> 19:24.862
         [ Music stops ]
            [ Crying ]

19:28.301 --> 19:30.635
        Sumo?
W-What are you doing here?

19:30.637 --> 19:32.603
Isn't the play happening
     right now?

19:32.605 --> 19:35.373
            N-No way. Everyone's
           gonna make fun of me.

19:35.375 --> 19:36.641
  Make fun of you?!

19:36.643 --> 19:39.143
Sumo, you're the best coyote
      there is!

19:39.145 --> 19:40.278
    Now, show me!

19:40.280 --> 19:41.712
   Make me scared!

19:41.714 --> 19:42.914
    Be a hunter!

19:44.450 --> 19:46.384
             [ Exhales sharply ]
             Ohh, I can't do it.

19:46.386 --> 19:48.886
               I can't do it.
               I can't do it.

19:49.822 --> 19:50.855
     Look at me.

19:50.857 --> 19:53.491
I'm just a little bunny,
just hopping around.

19:53.493 --> 19:55.193
  Who's gonna catch
     the bunny?

19:55.195 --> 19:56.561
Look at my little tail.

19:56.563 --> 19:59.163
I don't think you can catch
my tail, Mr. Co-yo-te.

19:59.165 --> 20:00.731
        Huh?
That's what I'm scared of.

20:00.733 --> 20:03.501
But I don't see one of those
around, do I? [ Chuckling ] Oh!

20:03.503 --> 20:06.671
 I'm a little bunny,
just hopping around...
         Come on, Jeff. Stop it!

20:06.673 --> 20:09.340
             Stupid bunny! Jeff!
  Who's gonna catch
     the bunny?

20:09.342 --> 20:10.541
   Ooh-oo-ooh!
                   [ Growls ]

20:10.543 --> 20:12.977
                   Where's
            that darn coyote at?

20:12.979 --> 20:15.680
  [ High-pitched ]
I'm hiding behind a rock.

20:15.682 --> 20:20.251
   I can't find him, even though
           I am looking for him.

20:20.253 --> 20:21.552
   Hee, hee, hee!

20:21.554 --> 20:23.754
Coyotes are the best!

20:23.756 --> 20:25.323
      [ Audience booing ]
            What...is happening?

20:25.325 --> 20:26.657
         What the biff?!

20:26.659 --> 20:28.559
       This is
more audience participation

20:28.561 --> 20:30.094
   than we've had
      in years!

20:30.096 --> 20:31.896
      A prodigy
    of the stage!

20:31.898 --> 20:33.331
      [ Doors burst open ]
           Yaaaaaaaaah!

20:33.333 --> 20:34.599
              Huh?

20:36.069 --> 20:37.902
   Oh, uh...naked?

20:37.904 --> 20:39.570
             Uhh...

20:39.572 --> 20:41.606
<i> Bold</i> costume choice.

20:44.244 --> 20:46.277
           [ Growls ]

20:46.279 --> 20:48.012
                 [ Giggles ]
                Scary puppy!

20:48.014 --> 20:49.547
           [ Growls ]

20:49.549 --> 20:52.583
     � I'm a hungry coyote,
         hear me growl �

20:52.585 --> 20:56.854
    [ Mid-tempo music plays ]
    � 'Cause it's eating time
   and I found me some chow �

20:56.856 --> 20:59.423
            [ Howls ]

20:59.425 --> 21:01.592
          [ Cheering ]

21:01.594 --> 21:04.395
     Ow-ow-awooooooooooooo!

21:04.397 --> 21:07.131
        [ Crowd howling ]

21:07.133 --> 21:08.566
                  But wait!

21:08.568 --> 21:11.068
              It's the firework
        from <i> before</i> in the play!

21:11.070 --> 21:12.069
                 I'm saved!

21:12.071 --> 21:14.238
        Oh!
Yes, yes, yes, yes!

21:14.240 --> 21:16.107
    [ Giggling ]

21:17.310 --> 21:19.210
              Rawr!

21:19.212 --> 21:20.211
           [ Grunts ]

21:20.213 --> 21:21.412
              Yah!

21:21.414 --> 21:23.080
          [ Cheering ]

21:23.082 --> 21:26.417
     [ Cheering continues ]
 Percy: Sumo! Sumo!
     Sumo! Sumo!

21:26.419 --> 21:29.754
     [ Laughing maniacally ]

21:29.756 --> 21:32.823
  [ Audience chanting "Sumo!" ]

21:32.825 --> 21:34.325
           [ Giggles ]

21:34.327 --> 21:37.028
          [ Giggling ]

21:39.165 --> 21:41.599
        Bravo. Oh, bravo.

21:41.601 --> 21:42.733
     [ Chanting continues ]

21:42.735 --> 21:45.569
                  Wo-o-o-w!
              Way to go, Sumo!

21:45.571 --> 21:47.772
     [ Chanting continues ]

21:47.774 --> 21:50.107
 We danced with defeat this day,

21:50.109 --> 21:52.443
    and <i> we</i> were the victors.

21:52.445 --> 21:53.444
             Bravo.

21:53.446 --> 21:54.445
            [ Creak ]

21:54.447 --> 21:55.980
       [ Screams, groans ]

21:57.283 --> 21:59.016
        � Early to bed �

22:00.653 --> 22:02.753
        � Early to rise �

22:04.290 --> 22:07.858
       � Picking my nose �

22:08.795 --> 22:10.761
          [ Whistles ]
